Like many people, I have a Sabya story. It was the year 2009 and I was a twenty five year old girl watching and unintentionally studying the works of design geniuses hitting the shop floor at Ensemble, while working with their in house design team. 
Fashion weeks were exciting and hanging out in the lounges meant you could’ve standing next to your idols. 
One such fashion week in one of the lounges, I met the man himself. I introduced myself and told him how much I admired his work and even though I was based in Bombay, I wanted to figure a way out to come and work for him and if he could give me a chance to do so. He smiled graciously, was receptive and without hesitation, said, “take my number down and call me when you’re ready to come.” Dumbfounded, I said, “really?” He said, “yes. If you’re passionate about working with us we’d be happy to have you.” It was a moment for me. And years later, it still evokes what it did then. I had that number for a few years. The universe, however, had other plans. 
25 glorious years of @sabyasachiofficial and the Bengal Tiger’s roar is echoing across the globe. 

From being the quintessential bridal designer of the country to bringing craft to the forefront, to celebrating heritage, to making us love our boat neck blouses and to making us own our deep cut ones as well, to making every bride in the country wear a maatha patti, to spelling out that “sexy is an energy, not an outfit, to creating Jewllery that remains Indian in craftsmanship but is truly global in inspiration and language, and lastly, to indulging the world with in your vision - here’s to a glorious and roaring 125 years and more ❤️✨🥂. 

Thank you for having me be a part a night celebrating the man, the brand, vision and the team @sabyasachiofficial @pareinathapar @longformgram ❤️✨.
